Colouration.
Head blackish brown, with pale yellow apex; eyes reddish brown, area surrounding ocellus reddish brown (
Figures 2E, G
, 
5C, D
). Antennae uniformly pale yellow, but male with apex of segment II and whole of segments III and IV with fuscous tinge (
Figure 5C, D
). Labium pale yellow; apex of segment IV somewhat fuscous (
Figure 2F, H
). Pronotum and scutellum uniformly blackish brown (
Figure 5C, D
). Hemelytra yellowish brown with cuneus widely darkened; membrane uniformly greyish brown (
Figure 2E, G
). Legs pale yellow; coxae and trochanters brown to blackish brown; tarsi pale yellow, with darkened apex (
Figure 2F, H
). Venter of thorax blackish brown. Abdomen brown to blackish brown (
Figure 2F, H
).
